The article discusses the importance of providing equal and quality education to Latino students in the United States. It highlights the 25th anniversary of the White House Initiative on Educational Excellence for Hispanics and the Year of Action that was launched in October 2014. The initiative challenges both the public and private sectors to make significant contributions to expand and support educational opportunities for the Latino community. The article also mentions several commitments made by different organizations and companies to invest in programs and initiatives aimed at improving educational outcomes for Latino students. These commitments include funding for participation in STEM education programs, expanding access to college preparation programs, supporting undocumented Latino students in their pursuit of higher education, promoting early childhood literacy, disaggregating national data to better understand educational disparities, and expanding the network of organizations that provide educational opportunities for Hispanic students. The article also mentions that federal agencies have responded to the initiative's call to action by investing in expanding access and opportunities for the Latino community.